### Request Body

For create and update operations, provide a JSON request body:

```bash
# Inline JSON
{{binaryName}} courses create --body '{"name": "My Course"}'

# From a file
{{binaryName}} courses create --body-file course.json

# From stdin
cat course.json | {{binaryName}} courses create
```

### Pagination

List commands auto-paginate by default. Control with:

```bash
# Limit results
{{binaryName}} courses list --limit 10

# Single page only
{{binaryName}} courses list --no-paginate
```

## ID Formats

Blackboard LMS supports multiple ID formats:

| Format | Example |
|--------|---------|
| Primary ID | `_123_1` |
| External ID | `externalId:COURSE-101` |
| Username | `userName:jdoe` |
| UUID | `uuid:abc-def-123` |

```bash
{{binaryName}} courses get _123_1
{{binaryName}} courses get externalId:CS-101
{{binaryName}} users get userName:jdoe
```

